Add a Table Widget to Show Record Details and Create Calculated Columns

You can add different types of tables to a CRM Analytics dashboard. To view record-level details, add a values table. A values table can show details like how long a case has been open and who owns it.

To create custom columns in a table based on calculations from existing fields, add a compare table. If the underlying query contains at least one grouping, you can create a pivot table.

Drag the table widget to the dashboard canvas.
Click the button inside the widget to open the wizard.

The Choose Data screen appears, showing the most recently used datasets first. Select the dataset in the Create Query tab or select an existing query in the Use Existing Query tab.

Select  and then choose the table type:

Values table: Use to show dataset fields as columns.
Compare table: Use to add calculated columns to the table.
Pivot table: Use to show groupings on the x- and y-axes.

For more information, see Creating Calculated Columns Using a Compare Table.

To quick sort on a column, click its field header. To add filters, click .

The widget shows the table and results. CRM Analytics adds the query to the query panel.

To change the widget and query properties, select the widget. The Widget panel groups the widget properties into sections.

To customize the appearance of the widget, set the widget properties. The widget properties vary based on the table type.

To preview your changes to the dashboard, click . Save the dashboard.

A table's groupings appear in the left columns and the measures appear in the right ones. You can scroll across the measures if needed.

Quick sort isnâ€™t available for tables with certain underlying queries:

* Compact-form query has interactions present on the sort order
* SAQL query contains union statements or interactions
* Query is in PIGQL
* Subtotals are enabled

See also: Widget Properties for Analytics Dashboard, Query Properties for Analytics Dashboard, Manage Queries for Widgets.
title: Adding Table Widgets to Salesforce CRM Analytics Dashboards
